

Transformer Text Style Prediction
=================================

This project demonstrates how to use a Transformer-based model to predict the writing style of a given text. 
The model can learn from a given sample and attempt to mimic its style, making it a great tool for experimenting with NLP and generative text tasks.

------------------------------------------------------------
Features
------------------------------------------------------------

- Transformer-based text style predictor
- Simple web interface to test the model (index.html)
- Custom training on any text you provide
- Outputs text in the learned style

------------------------------------------------------------
Prerequisites
------------------------------------------------------------

Before running the project, make sure you have the following installed:

- Python 3.7+
- Required Python libraries (install using the command below):

    pip install -r requirements.txt

If you don't have a requirements.txt, hereâ€™s a basic one you can add:

    transformers
    torch
    flask

------------------------------------------------------------
How to Run
------------------------------------------------------------

1. Clone the repository

    git clone https://github.com/aditya9515/Transformer_Text_Style_Prediction.git
    cd Transformer_Text_Style_Prediction

2. Start the Flask backend

    python main.py

3. Open the web interface

    Simply open index.html in your browser.

4. Use the app

    - Copy and paste the text you want the model to learn from.
    - Click to train and generate the output in the same style.

